CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 24, 1959, pg. 3 reads: "Firebug's Work - The home where the Dupree children died (right) is in tinderbox area in the "bottoms" of Braddock where three fires within one week have led police and firemen to suspect arson."
TitMainTitle: Framed home destroyed by fire, 1228 Washington Street, Braddock
